---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/vue/Footer.vue';
import Header from '../components/vue/Header.vue';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - PM-Panel">
    <!-- Header -->
    <Header client:only="vue" />

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="legal-content">
                <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
                <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2024</p>

                <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
                <p>By accessing or using PM-Panel, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our service.</p>

                <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
                <p>PM-Panel is a project management platform designed for freelancers and small teams to organize client work, track project status, and facilitate communication. Features include project creation, status tracking, note-taking, file attachments, and client portal sharing.</p>

                <h2>3. Account Registration</h2>
                <h3>3.1 Eligibility</h3>
                <p>You must be at least 18 years old to create an account. By registering, you represent that you have the legal capacity to enter into these terms.</p>

                <h3>3.2 Account Security</h3>
                <p>You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials. Notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account. We are not liable for any loss or damage arising from your failure to secure your account.</p>

                <h3>3.3 Account Information</h3>
                <p>You agree to provide accurate and complete information during registration and to keep this information updated. We reserve the right to suspend accounts with false information.</p>

                <h2>4. Acceptable Use</h2>
                <p>You agree not to use PM-Panel to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Upload or share illegal, harmful, or infringing content</li>
                    <li>Harass, abuse, or harm other users</li>
                    <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems</li>
                    <li>Use automated scripts or bots without permission</li>
                    <li>Interfere with the proper functioning of the service</li>
                    <li>Resell or sublicense access to the platform</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>5. Data and Content</h2>
                <h3>5.1 Your Content</h3>
                <p>You retain all rights to the content you upload to PM-Panel, including project names, notes, and file attachments. You grant us a limited license to host and display this content solely for the purpose of providing our service.</p>

                <h3>5.2 Client Data</h3>
                <p>You are responsible for obtaining appropriate consent from your clients before adding their information to PM-Panel. You must comply with applicable data protection laws when processing client data.</p>

                <h3>5.3 Data Removal</h3>
                <p>We reserve the right to remove content that violates these terms or applicable laws. You may delete your own content and projects at any time.</p>

                <h2>6. Service Availability</h2>
                <p>We strive to maintain 99.9% uptime but do not guarantee uninterrupted service. We may perform maintenance that temporarily affects availability. We are not liable for any damages resulting from service interruptions.</p>

                <h2>7. Modifications to Service</h2>
                <p>We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the service at any time. We will provide notice of significant changes when possible.</p>

                <h2>8. Termination</h2>
                <h3>8.1 By You</h3>
                <p>You may delete your account at any time. Upon deletion, your data will be permanently removed according to our data retention policies.</p>

                <h3>8.2 By Us</h3>
                <p>We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these terms, engage in fraudulent activity, or use the service in a way that harms others.</p>

                <h2>9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
                <p>PM-Panel is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We do not warrant that the service will be error-free, secure, or meet your specific requirements.</p>

                <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
                <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, PM-Panel and its creators shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including loss of profits, data, or business opportunities, arising from your use of the service.</p>

                <h2>11. Indemnification</h2>
                <p>You agree to indemnify and hold harmless PM-Panel from any claims, damages, or expenses arising from your use of the service, your content, or your violation of these terms.</p>

                <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
                <p>These terms shall be governed by the laws of [Your Jurisdiction]. Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of [Your Jurisdiction].</p>

                <h2>13. Changes to Terms</h2>
                <p>We may update these terms from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes via email or through the platform. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.</p>

                <h2>14. Contact</h2>
                <p>For questions about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@pm-panel.com">legal@pm-panel.com</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <Footer client:only="vue" />
</Layout>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/fix.css">

<style>
    .section {
        padding: 60px 0;
    }

    .legal-content {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .legal-content h1 {
        font-size: 36px;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .last-updated {
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        font-size: 14px;
        margin-bottom: 32px;
    }

    .legal-content h2 {
        font-size: 22px;
        margin-top: 32px;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .legal-content h3 {
        font-size: 18px;
        margin-top: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    }

    .legal-content p {
        color: var(--color-text-secondary);
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .legal-content ul {
        padding-left: 24px;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .legal-content li {
        color: var(--color-text-secondary);
        padding: 4px 0;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .legal-content a {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .legal-content h1 {
            font-size: 28px;
        }
    }
</style>
